name: UAudioImpulseResponse
doc:
UAudioImpulseResponse
UAsset used to represent Imported Impulse Responses

NormalizationVolumeDb: Used to account for energy added by convolution with "loud" Impulse Responses.
bTrueStereo: If true, impulse response channels are interpreted as true stereo which allows channel crosstalk. If false, impulse response channels are interpreted as independent channel impulses.
